\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy establishes mandatory requirements for the protection of Criminal Justice Information (CJI),
 Personally Identifiable Information (PII),
 and Protected Health Information (PHI,
 where applicable) processed,
 stored,
 or transmitted by or on behalf of Elko County.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
2.
 Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy applies to all County Personnel — including employees,
 elected officials,
 contractors,
 vendors,
 interns,
 and volunteers — who access,
 use,
 collect,
 store,
 process,
 or transmit CJI,
 PII,
 or PHI.
 This policy applies regardless of location,
 medium,
 or funding source,
 and regardless of whether the data is held in County-owned,
 County-managed,
 or County-provisioned systems and services.
\end_layout

