\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
6.
 Policy Statement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy governs the County's privacy-specific controls and the Privacy Impact Assessment (PIA) process.
 General data classification,
 storage,
 retention,
 access mechanics,
 media sanitization,
 and incident execution remain governed by their respective policies cross-referenced throughout this policy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
6.1 Privacy Impact Assessments
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Privacy Impact Assessment (PIA) is the County's authoritative instrument for identifying and disposing of privacy risk before data is collected,
 processed,
 or shared.
 A PIA is not exclusive to formally designated projects;
 it applies to any change in the County's privacy posture that meets the trigger conditions below.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Trigger Events
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall approve a PIA before any of the following events proceed:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
A new system that will process,
 store,
 or transmit CJI,
 PII,
 or PHI.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
A modification to an existing system processing CJI,
 PII,
 or PHI that introduces a new data category,
 a new storage location,
 an expanded access population,
 or a new data recipient.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
A new data collection that introduces a category of personal information the County did not previously collect.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
A new data-sharing arrangement under which CJI,
 PII,
 or PHI is shared with an external party.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Reclassification of data upward under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.11"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 when the new classification is Confidential or Restricted.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
A change in processing purpose for personal information already collected that exceeds or contradicts the legal authority under which the data was originally collected,
 expands data use into a category not previously authorized,
 or is inconsistent with any public notice of collection provided to data subjects.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
PIA Content
\series default
:
 The Assistant IT Director shall ensure each PIA addresses the following items at minimum:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Data categories involved (CJI,
 PII,
 PHI),
 approximate record count or estimated data volume,
 and sources.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Legal authority for collection,
 processing,
 use,
 or disclosure,
 including the specific statute,
 regulation,
 ordinance,
 court order,
 agreement,
 grant condition,
 or documented County business function under which the data is authorized.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Processing purpose and consistency with the purpose of original collection.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Data flow,
 storage locations,
 and transmission paths.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Access control posture and role eligibility.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Retention disposition aligned with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.11"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Sharing arrangements and recipient controls.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Privacy risks identified,
 compensating controls applied,
 and residual risk accepted.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Approval Authority
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall approve all PIAs.
 PIA approval authority is not subject to Directed Deputization under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.08"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
